{
  "texts": [
    "Large language models show remarkable zero-shot capabilities by simply learning to predict the next token at scale (Brown et al., 2020; Touvron et al., 2023).",
    "By fine-tuning these models on instruction tuning datasets containing many tasks-each comprising an input instruction and a desired response-the model generally improves in its ability to respond to unseen instructions.",
    "However, this generalization is still limited by the qualities of the instruction tuning dataset.",
    "Existing datasets like Public Pool of Prompts (P3) (Bach et al., 2022), Natural Instructions (Mishra et al., 2022; Wang et al., 2022), and Dolly-v2 (Conover et al., 2023) focus on text from the Web and classic natural language tasks so that they can serve a wide range of use cases, i.e., they are a one-size-fits-all approach.",
    "On the other hand, tasks in areas like biomedical and legal domains require specialized, often implicit, domain knowledge."
  ]
}